[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_ishui")
reagent_id = "CaS"
title = "Calcium sulfide"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]CaS[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]72 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Solid[/cell]
[cell]Color:[/cell][cell]White to light gray[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reactions[/b]
Ca + S → CaS  
Ca + H₂S → CaS  
Ca(OH)₂ + H₂S → CaS + 2H₂O  
CaO + H₂S → CaS + H₂O
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Ionic compound made of calcium and sulfur ions.  
• Reacts with water and acids to produce hydrogen sulfide gas (H₂S).  
• Sensitive to moisture in air.
[b]Where calcium sulfide is found[/b]
• Produced when calcium compounds react with sulfur at high temperature.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Used in phosphorescent materials (glow-in-the-dark paints).  
• Used in some chemical processes.
[b]Safety[/b]
Can release toxic hydrogen sulfide gas when reacting with water or acids.  
Should be handled in dry conditions."
